-I don't know.

52
00:03:00.138 --> 00:03:02.432
The divisions. they're happening
in our neighborhoods.

53
00:03:02.515 --> 00:03:03.808
they're happening
in our schools.

54
00:03:03.892 --> 00:03:06.227
and they're happening
in our families.

55
00:03:06.269 --> 00:03:08.563
It wasn't that they just had
political disagreements.

56
00:03:08.605 --> 00:03:12.192
Folks were physically attacking
one another.

57
00:03:12.233 --> 00:03:14.527
Stop!

58
00:03:14.569 --> 00:03:16.154
Stop!

59
00:03:16.237 --> 00:03:17.405
♪

60
00:03:17.488 --> 00:03:20.617
The root causes of division
go all the way down

61
00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:23.203
into our foundation
as a country.

62
00:03:23.244 --> 00:03:27.624
We're facing problems
we've never faced before.

63
00:03:27.707 --> 00:03:29.918
(shouting)

64
00:03:30.001 --> 00:03:31.169
If we're going to live
in a democracy.

65
00:03:31.252 --> 00:03:32.754
all of us have to learn
to be mediators

66
00:03:32.795 --> 00:03:34.505
and bridge-builders.

67
00:03:34.589 --> 00:03:35.715
I'm Steven Olikara.

68
00:03:35.757 --> 00:03:37.425
My name is Susan Bro.

69
00:03:37.508 --> 00:03:38.593
I'm Greg Orman.

70
00:03:38.635 --> 00:03:40.136
I'm Mark Gerzon. I'm the author

71
00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:42.305
of The Reunited States
of America.

72
00:03:42.388 --> 00:03:44.182
and I've been a bridge-builder

73
00:03:44.265 --> 00:03:46.100
between Democrats
and Republicans

74
00:03:46.142 --> 00:03:48.728
in the partisan divide
for the last 30 years.

75
00:03:48.770 --> 00:03:50.772
What I've learned
is that polarization

76
00:03:50.813 --> 00:03:53.149
is not just in Washington.
it's in our own hearts.

77
00:03:53.233 --> 00:03:56.277
Before we can fix government.
we have to fix ourselves

78
00:03:56.319 --> 00:03:58.905
and the way we see
our fellow citizens.

79
00:03:58.947 --> 00:04:01.991
-We're Erin...
-...and David Leaverton.

80
00:04:02.075 --> 00:04:04.619
We decided to travel
to all 50 states

81
00:04:04.661 --> 00:04:05.870
to get an understanding

82
00:04:05.954 --> 00:04:09.290
of what was causing
these divisions.

83
00:04:09.332 --> 00:04:11.501
The real key to solving
the partisan divide

84
00:04:11.584 --> 00:04:12.961
is within each of us.

85
00:04:13.044 --> 00:04:15.463
That's part of being a citizen
of America.

86
00:04:15.505 --> 00:04:17.131
We are the solution.

87
00:04:17.173 --> 00:04:20.301
Ordinary citizens working
across the divide every day

88
00:04:20.385 --> 00:04:22.887
to make this country
a better place.

89
00:04:22.971 --> 00:04:26.140
Whether it's a liberal agenda
or a conservative agenda.

90
00:04:26.224 --> 00:04:29.686
hate does not belong
to either one.

91
00:04:29.769 --> 00:04:30.937
We're always gonna
have liberals

92
00:04:30.979 --> 00:04:32.230
and conservatives in America.

93
00:04:32.313 --> 00:04:34.607
We'll never make
the other side go away.

94
00:04:34.649 --> 00:04:36.818
It's in our own interest

95
00:04:36.859 --> 00:04:39.237
to learn how to cross
the divide.

96
00:04:39.320 --> 00:04:40.321
We are the government.

97
00:04:40.363 --> 00:04:42.657
If we want to see
a different government.

98
00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:43.950
the genius of America

99
00:04:43.992 --> 00:04:47.328
is that it's our responsibility
to fix it.

100
00:04:47.370 --> 00:04:49.163
♪

101
00:04:49.205 --> 00:04:51.249
We need a narrative
about the left and the right

102
00:04:51.332 --> 00:04:52.500
working together.

103
00:04:52.542 --> 00:04:55.295
This is something
we have the power to change.

104
00:04:55.336 --> 00:04:58.339
This is something
we have control over.

105
00:04:58.423 --> 00:05:01.843
I want to create a third force
in our politics

106
00:05:01.926 --> 00:05:05.888
that's able to get us beyond
this partisan warfare.

107
00:05:05.972 --> 00:05:07.932
This country needs
bridge-builders.

108
00:05:08.016 --> 00:05:11.352
people who have the courage
to be pioneers.

109
00:05:11.436 --> 00:05:13.354
who are willing to get out
of their comfort zones

110
00:05:13.438 --> 00:05:15.189
to bring both sides together.

111
00:05:15.273 --> 00:05:17.066
That's the path forward.

112
00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:27.076
♪

113
00:05:28.870 --> 00:05:31.789
Mary Catherine.
what are you drawing?

114
00:05:31.873 --> 00:05:35.043
-I'm making our bus.
-Are you really?

115
00:05:35.126 --> 00:05:36.627
-Yes.
-Look at it.

116
00:05:36.711 --> 00:05:38.004
Very beautiful.

117
00:05:38.046 --> 00:05:39.589
And where is it going?

118
00:05:39.672 --> 00:05:42.216
To all the states.

119
00:05:42.258 --> 00:05:44.552
To all the states.

120
00:05:44.635 --> 00:05:46.721
-Are you excited?
-Yeah.

121
00:05:46.763 --> 00:05:48.723
Cool. me too.

122
00:05:48.765 --> 00:05:50.641
-Very aerodynamic.
-Mm-hm.

123
00:05:50.725 --> 00:05:53.561
I like it.

124
00:05:53.603 --> 00:05:55.438
♪

125
00:05:55.521 --> 00:05:58.232
I always felt like
when I left politics

126
00:05:58.274 --> 00:06:02.403
that there were some things
that were left unfinished.

127
00:06:02.445 --> 00:06:05.865
I was a proud Republican.
and I was working

128
00:06:05.907 --> 00:06:08.743
to defeat any Democrat
who was in our way

129
00:06:08.826 --> 00:06:13.498
because I really felt like
what their policies were doing

130
00:06:13.581 --> 00:06:16.334
was destroying our country.

131
00:06:16.417 --> 00:06:18.127
♪

132
00:06:18.211 --> 00:06:20.630
Did everything
from opposition research

133
00:06:20.713 --> 00:06:22.090
to targeted campaigns

134
00:06:22.131 --> 00:06:24.759
that would turn
one group of voters

135
00:06:24.842 --> 00:06:27.804
against another group
of voters.

136
00:06:27.887 --> 00:06:31.057
I was involved in things
I'm not really proud of.

137
00:06:31.099 --> 00:06:32.475
♪

138
00:06:32.558 --> 00:06:36.354
People are getting inundated
with this message of division

139
00:06:36.437 --> 00:06:38.815
and dehumanization
and demonization

140
00:06:38.898 --> 00:06:41.818
of the other side.
and it is tearing families apart

141
00:06:41.901 --> 00:06:45.113
and it's tearing
communities apart.

142
00:06:45.196 --> 00:06:47.573
I've been involved in
those kind of campaigns

143
00:06:47.615 --> 00:06:49.617
and I know how to do that.

144
00:06:49.700 --> 00:06:54.914
♪

145
00:06:54.956 --> 00:06:58.376
So. fast forward to 2016.
we were watching

146
00:06:58.459 --> 00:07:01.921
a story about this guy
who got hit across the head

147
00:07:01.963 --> 00:07:04.590
with a bag of rocks
because he was wearing

148
00:07:04.632 --> 00:07:07.385
a Make America Great Again hat.

149
00:07:07.468 --> 00:07:09.345
♪

150
00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:13.599
I sensed a deep sort of sorrow
growing in him.

151
00:07:13.641 --> 00:07:15.143
♪

152
00:07:15.184 --> 00:07:17.645
And one night. I just said.

153
00:07:17.728 --> 00:07:19.147
"If you didn't have a mortgage.

154
00:07:19.188 --> 00:07:21.524
what would you want
to wake up and do tomorrow?"

155
00:07:21.607 --> 00:07:25.862
And I answered her.
"To bring unity to America."

156
00:07:25.945 --> 00:07:29.740
It came out before
I even thought about it.

157
00:07:29.824 --> 00:07:31.826
I was like. "How are you
gonna bring unity

158
00:07:31.909 --> 00:07:35.121
to people you've never met?"

159
00:07:35.163 --> 00:07:37.248
♪

160
00:07:37.331 --> 00:07:39.041
Okay. Now where's
the wrapping paper?

161
00:07:39.125 --> 00:07:42.336
-You got a Sharpie?
-Uh-huh.

162
00:07:42.378 --> 00:07:43.171
♪

163
00:07:43.254 --> 00:07:46.132
So at 5:00 a.m..
she wakes me up.

164
00:07:46.174 --> 00:07:48.885
And I said. "You know.
what if the first step

165
00:07:48.968 --> 00:07:50.386
of learning about division

166
00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.889
is to go out
and actually ask people?"

167
00:07:52.972 --> 00:07:54.891
I said. "You're crazy.

168
00:07:54.974 --> 00:07:56.642
but I can't think
of a better way

169
00:07:56.684 --> 00:07:58.769
to learn about what's broken
in our country."

170
00:07:58.853 --> 00:08:01.647
Hey. guys. we've got an
exciting announcement to make.

171
00:08:01.689 --> 00:08:03.483
We've gone crazy.

172
00:08:03.524 --> 00:08:06.736
I quit my job.
we sold our house.

173
00:08:06.819 --> 00:08:08.362
and we bought an RV.

174
00:08:08.446 --> 00:08:12.074
We're going on a great
American road trip for a year

175
00:08:12.158 --> 00:08:14.368
to all 50 states
with our family of five.

176
00:08:14.452 --> 00:08:16.746
Our goal for this year
is to reach outside our bubble.

177
00:08:16.829 --> 00:08:19.582
to host dinners and to listen
and learn from people

178
00:08:19.665 --> 00:08:20.625
who aren't like us...

179
00:08:20.708 --> 00:08:22.627
Hi. big bus.

180
00:08:22.710 --> 00:08:26.756
...and hopefully discover
what connects us as Americans.

181
00:08:26.839 --> 00:08:28.049
♪

182
00:08:28.090 --> 00:08:29.383
Come along for the ride.

183
00:08:29.425 --> 00:08:31.344
It'll be fun.

184
00:08:31.385 --> 00:08:38.351
♪

185
00:08:58.746 --> 00:09:01.249
(sharp exhaling)

186
00:09:05.962 --> 00:09:08.589
She was still alive.

187
00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:17.306
She was still alive
a year ago right now.

188
00:09:19.058 --> 00:09:22.103
She was hot. she was tired.
she was thirsty.

189
00:09:22.186 --> 00:09:25.481
She was still alive.

190
00:09:25.565 --> 00:09:27.108
♪

191
00:09:27.149 --> 00:09:28.901
My daughter was not a leader.

192
00:09:28.943 --> 00:09:32.613
She was not a known activist.

193
00:09:32.655 --> 00:09:33.864
♪

194
00:09:33.948 --> 00:09:36.242
He just drove into a crowd.

195
00:09:36.284 --> 00:09:40.955
and she was the one
who happened to die.

196
00:09:41.038 --> 00:09:45.459
♪

197
00:09:45.501 --> 00:09:48.004
Thank you for coming
to remember Heather.

198
00:09:48.087 --> 00:09:50.631
but this was not
all about Heather.

199
00:09:50.673 --> 00:09:54.635
We have a huge problem
in our city and in our country.

200
00:09:54.719 --> 00:09:56.178
We have got to fix this

201
00:09:56.262 --> 00:09:59.140
or we'll be right back here
in no time.

202
00:09:59.223 --> 00:10:01.559
The world went crazy
when Heather lost her life.

203
00:10:01.642 --> 00:10:04.812
and that's not fair
because so many mothers lose

204
00:10:04.895 --> 00:10:09.317
their children every day.
and we have to fix that.

205
00:10:09.358 --> 00:10:13.154
I don't want other mothers
to be in my spot.

206
00:10:13.237 --> 00:10:16.240
I don't want other mothers
to go through this.

207
00:10:16.324 --> 00:10:18.159
♪

208
00:10:18.200 --> 00:10:21.621
So. today. not only
do we remember my baby girl.

209
00:10:21.662 --> 00:10:24.999
I want to thank the troopers
for their sacrifice

210
00:10:25.082 --> 00:10:27.335
who lost their lives that day.

211
00:10:27.376 --> 00:10:29.879
There's so much healing to do

212
00:10:29.962 --> 00:10:31.505
and we've got to do it together.

213
00:10:31.589 --> 00:10:33.341
Amen.

214
00:10:33.382 --> 00:10:35.551
♪

215
00:10:35.635 --> 00:10:40.097
I struggle with my own
emotional issues.

216
00:10:40.181 --> 00:10:43.059
Heather died.
but there were 30 people

217
00:10:43.142 --> 00:10:44.310
who were injured that day

218
00:10:44.352 --> 00:10:48.564
who are having
a really hard time.

219
00:10:48.648 --> 00:10:50.524
-I need to tell you something.
-Yes. dear.

220
00:10:50.608 --> 00:10:52.360
-It's about Heather.
-Yes?

221
00:10:52.401 --> 00:10:56.364
I stood there with her
as she went...

222
00:10:56.405 --> 00:10:57.990
♪

223
00:10:58.032 --> 00:11:00.701
She went well.

224
00:11:00.785 --> 00:11:02.203
♪

225
00:11:02.286 --> 00:11:03.871
I believe it.

226
00:11:03.954 --> 00:11:06.374
Thank you.

227
00:11:06.415 --> 00:11:09.085
I was the street medic
who was the first responder

228
00:11:09.168 --> 00:11:10.252
for Heather
and initiated CPR...

229
00:11:12.838 --> 00:11:14.173
I do. I just wanted you to know

230
00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:15.216
I did everything
that I could do.

231
00:11:15.299 --> 00:11:17.301
Thank you. I understand.

232
00:11:17.385 --> 00:11:20.429
but this is the way
it was meant to be. sadly.

233
00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:23.140
Heather would never want
this attention on her.

234
00:11:23.224 --> 00:11:26.143
The attention belongs
squarely on the issues

235
00:11:26.227 --> 00:11:29.355
that she was standing up for
that day.

236
00:11:29.397 --> 00:11:30.940
Thirty-two-year-old
Heather Heyer

237
00:11:31.023 --> 00:11:33.526
was protesting white supremacy.

238
00:11:33.567 --> 00:11:35.778
The statue of Confederate
General Robert E. Lee

239
00:11:35.861 --> 00:11:37.363
has become the focal point

240
00:11:37.405 --> 00:11:41.242
since the city council voted
in February to remove it.

241
00:11:41.325 --> 00:11:45.746
I did not pay attention
to politics before Heather died.

242
00:11:45.830 --> 00:11:47.289
♪

243
00:11:47.373 --> 00:11:52.586
I thought the country
was healed over racial issues.

244
00:11:52.670 --> 00:11:56.382
♪

245
00:11:56.424 --> 00:11:59.927
I just didn't understand
how deeply it went.

246
00:12:00.010 --> 00:12:02.430
♪

247
00:12:02.513 --> 00:12:06.267
You know. it's difficult
to explain to a child

248
00:12:06.308 --> 00:12:10.271
why the Lee statue
still stands.

249
00:12:10.354 --> 00:12:14.108
Even at eight years old.

250
00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:17.737
they recognize the Lee statue

251
00:12:17.778 --> 00:12:20.948
as a civil rights issue.

252
00:12:21.031 --> 00:12:23.075
I did not seek
this opportunity.

253
00:12:23.117 --> 00:12:25.453
I'm just trying to make
something positive

254
00:12:25.536 --> 00:12:28.998
out of this horrible situation.

255
00:12:29.081 --> 00:12:32.251
My daughter. who was not
a known activist.

256
00:12:32.293 --> 00:12:36.797
would tell you as I am
telling you. get over her.

257
00:12:36.839 --> 00:12:40.468
Let's get on to the issues
that she died for.

258
00:12:40.509 --> 00:12:45.473
She died for lives mattering.

259
00:12:45.556 --> 00:12:47.892
(applause)

260
00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:51.937
All of us have to find
what our way

261
00:12:51.979 --> 00:12:53.898
of caring about each other is.

262
00:12:53.981 --> 00:12:55.983
Amen.

263
00:12:56.025 --> 00:12:59.028
I'm trying to figure out
what I'm supposed to be doing.

264
