1000
00:45:58.130 --> 00:45:59.965
that no mother
ever wants to join

1001
00:46:00.048 --> 00:46:02.050
where you have a child

1002
00:46:02.134 --> 00:46:04.303
who is removed from your life.

1003
00:46:04.344 --> 00:46:06.680
She was just 32 years old.

1004
00:46:06.764 --> 00:46:08.307
finding her voice.

1005
00:46:08.390 --> 00:46:09.725
She showed up.

1006
00:46:09.808 --> 00:46:12.269
You say. "Okay.
that happened a year ago.

1007
00:46:12.311 --> 00:46:13.979
What does that have
to do with anything?"

1008
00:46:14.021 --> 00:46:16.482
Well. here's what I would like
you to take away from this.

1009
00:46:16.523 --> 00:46:19.485
There is a great divide
in our country.

1010
00:46:19.568 --> 00:46:22.112
and I think it's
probably a good thing.

1011
00:46:22.154 --> 00:46:24.364
We're finally looking at issues

1012
00:46:24.448 --> 00:46:26.158
that we have glossed over.

1013
00:46:26.241 --> 00:46:27.826
What I hear from people of color

1014
00:46:27.910 --> 00:46:31.163
is white people annoy
the heck out of 'em

1015
00:46:31.205 --> 00:46:33.499
when they say.
"I don't see color.

1016
00:46:33.582 --> 00:46:35.709
Race isn't important to me.

1017
00:46:35.793 --> 00:46:37.294
All lives matter."

1018
00:46:37.336 --> 00:46:39.296
because how it
sounds to them is

1019
00:46:39.338 --> 00:46:41.965
"I have to see you
as another white person

1020
00:46:42.007 --> 00:46:43.509
in order to accept you."

1021
00:46:43.592 --> 00:46:45.677
I used to say those same things.

1022
00:46:45.761 --> 00:46:47.888
What they would
like us to say is.

1023
00:46:47.971 --> 00:46:50.599
"I see your color.
I see your heritage.

1024
00:46:50.682 --> 00:46:53.852
I recognize them.
I celebrate them with you."

1025
00:46:53.936 --> 00:46:55.938
And therein lies the difference.

1026
00:46:56.021 --> 00:46:57.564
Be willing to understand

1027
00:46:57.648 --> 00:47:02.528
we as white people have had
a free ride in a lot of ways.

1028
00:47:02.569 --> 00:47:06.114
even if we've struggled
from poverty all the way up.

1029
00:47:06.198 --> 00:47:07.783
We still have
layers of protection

1030
00:47:07.866 --> 00:47:10.869
that other people
don't necessarily have.

1031
00:47:10.953 --> 00:47:12.162
So we have to rethink

1032
00:47:12.204 --> 00:47:14.373
a lot of the structures
of our country.

1033
00:47:14.414 --> 00:47:15.666
Simply glossing over.

1034
00:47:15.707 --> 00:47:17.334
and everybody
hugging each other

1035
00:47:17.376 --> 00:47:20.712
and singing Kumbaya
is not gonna solve anything.

1036
00:47:20.796 --> 00:47:23.757
We have some serious
issues to work on.

1037
00:47:23.841 --> 00:47:26.385
♪

1038
