1267
00:57:58.391 --> 00:58:01.895
♪

1268
00:58:01.978 --> 00:58:03.563
My process for
becoming an independent

1269
00:58:03.646 --> 00:58:06.858
has occurred over
a long period of time.

1270
00:58:06.900 --> 00:58:10.695
My dad was a Republican.
and my mother was a Democrat.

1271
00:58:10.778 --> 00:58:13.239
Becoming an independent
may have been a way to bridge

1272
00:58:13.323 --> 00:58:17.660
the divide between
my mother and my father.

1273
00:58:17.702 --> 00:58:19.329
Greg always uses the analogy of

1274
00:58:19.370 --> 00:58:22.415
a couple going through
a bitter divorce.

1275
00:58:22.499 --> 00:58:23.291
We've gotten to a point

1276
00:58:27.712 --> 00:58:29.005
and maybe we need a mediator.

1277
00:58:29.047 --> 00:58:30.465
and maybe that's what

1278
00:58:30.548 --> 00:58:33.218
independent
politicians could be.

1279
00:58:33.259 --> 00:58:35.595
This is my daughter Imogen.

1280
00:58:35.678 --> 00:58:37.889
The average American family

1281
00:58:37.931 --> 00:58:39.766
