00:59:03.540 --> 00:59:05.708
♪

1293
00:59:05.750 --> 00:59:07.544
When we were getting
the Millennial Action Project

1294
00:59:07.585 --> 00:59:08.670
off the ground.

1295
00:59:08.753 --> 00:59:10.255
of course there was
a lot of skepticism.

1296
00:59:10.338 --> 00:59:13.716
They thought this idea
of bringing people together

1297
00:59:13.758 --> 00:59:16.886
across party lines and
empowering young legislators

1298
00:59:16.928 --> 00:59:18.680
was too idealistic.

1299
00:59:18.763 --> 00:59:21.349
♪

1300
00:59:21.432 --> 00:59:23.685
Some people.
without even meeting.

1301
00:59:23.768 --> 00:59:25.520
would close the door.

1302
00:59:25.603 --> 00:59:29.190
People were looking
for reasons to dismiss us.

1303
00:59:29.274 --> 00:59:32.110
♪

1304
00:59:32.151 --> 00:59:36.781
I was 23 when we were
getting it off the ground.

1305
00:59:36.823 --> 00:59:38.575
I did have some moments
where I felt

1306
00:59:38.616 --> 00:59:41.703
"Why do I think I can
do anything about this

1307
00:59:41.786 --> 00:59:43.538
huge problem?"

1308
00:59:43.621 --> 00:59:46.541
♪

1309
00:59:46.624 --> 00:59:50.628
I think people are often
quick to dismiss

1310
00:59:50.712 --> 00:59:52.463
bold new ideas.

1311
00:59:52.505 --> 00:59:55.091
and even quicker
to dismiss those ideas

1312
00:59:55.133 --> 00:59:58.595
if it comes from young people.

1313
00:59:58.636 --> 01:00:01.014
Our bold new idea
is the bold new idea

1314
01:00:01.097 --> 01:00:02.515
of the founding of the country.

1315
01:00:02.599 --> 01:00:05.852
which is
an E Pluribus Unum society.

1316
01:00:05.935 --> 01:00:07.604
"Out of many. one."

1317
01:00:07.645 --> 01:00:10.315
♪

1318
01:00:10.356 --> 01:00:11.399
As Bobby Kennedy said.

1319
01:00:13.776 --> 01:00:16.821
and the greatest
stake in the future."

1320
01:00:16.863 --> 01:00:20.366
So it's really important to
listen to the next generation.

1321
01:00:20.450 --> 01:00:25.371
♪

1322
01:00:25.455 --> 01:00:30.627
We're on our way
to the first day of the trial.

1323
01:00:30.668 --> 01:00:34.172
I don't really expect
any sort of closure from this.

1324
01:00:34.255 --> 01:00:37.634
If it stops somebody else
from doing the same thing.

1325
01:00:37.675 --> 01:00:40.511
then it's worthwhile.

1326
01:00:40.595 --> 01:00:42.180
The man accused
of ramming his car

1327
01:00:42.263 --> 01:00:43.890
into a crowd appeared in court.

1328
01:00:43.973 --> 01:00:47.018
Now. this is expected to be
a high-profile case.

1329
01:00:47.060 --> 01:00:48.978
It's expected
to last three weeks.

1330
01:00:49.020 --> 01:00:51.022
If convicted.
one of those charges

1331
01:00:51.064 --> 01:00:54.525
could result in
the death penalty.

1332
01:00:54.567 --> 01:00:56.778
I don't hate him.

1333
01:00:56.861 --> 01:00:58.029
Hate is caustic

1334
01:00:58.112 --> 01:01:01.699
to the person who hates.

1335
01:01:01.741 --> 01:01:03.034
I'm glad I'm not the one

1336
01:01:03.117 --> 01:01:06.788
who has to place
judgment on him 'cause...

1337
01:01:08.915 --> 01:01:12.126
...he murdered my child.

1338
01:01:12.210 --> 01:01:15.672
Her loss is a hole
in the family.

1339
01:01:15.713 --> 01:01:17.507
It's a hole in my heart.

1340
01:01:17.548 --> 01:01:22.553
It's a hole in every
celebration that we have.

1341
01:01:22.595 --> 01:01:24.472
It's not right
that people had to wait

1342
01:01:24.555 --> 01:01:26.099
till a white girl was killed

1343
01:01:26.182 --> 01:01:29.227
to go "There's a problem."

1344
01:01:29.268 --> 01:01:30.728
Heather got all this attention.

1345
01:01:30.770 --> 01:01:32.188
but too many mothers

1346
01:01:32.230 --> 01:01:34.899
are going through this
all the time.

1347
01:01:34.982 --> 01:01:41.364
♪

1348
01:01:41.406 --> 01:01:43.616
That corner. guys.
or this corner?

1349
01:01:43.700 --> 01:01:45.076
♪

1350
01:01:45.159 --> 01:01:48.454
How 'bout right here?

1351
01:01:48.538 --> 01:01:49.789
Good afternoon.

1352
01:01:49.872 --> 01:01:52.750
A United States district judge
determined that

1353
01:01:52.834 --> 01:01:55.253
Mr. Fields deserved to spend

1354
01:01:55.294 --> 01:01:57.839
the rest of his life
in federal prison.

1355
01:01:57.922 --> 01:02:01.300
and imposed that sentence.

1356
01:02:01.384 --> 01:02:03.845
Susan. what do you think?

1357
01:02:03.928 --> 01:02:07.056
I'm very happy he got
life in prison across the board.

1358
01:02:07.098 --> 01:02:08.933
I did not want
the death penalty.

1359
01:02:09.016 --> 01:02:10.893
Blood on my hands.

1360
01:02:10.935 --> 01:02:14.439
Did this sentence help you?

1361
01:02:14.480 --> 01:02:16.357
Knowing that he won't
be out again

1362
01:02:16.441 --> 01:02:19.318
to cause more harm
to more people helps.

1363
01:02:19.402 --> 01:02:22.196
Knowing that a clear
message has been sent

1364
01:02:22.280 --> 01:02:25.324
hoping to prevent
other deaths. that helps.

1365
01:02:25.408 --> 01:02:28.411
The last time I saw my daughter
was to identify her body.

1366
01:02:28.453 --> 01:02:31.456
and I held her bruised hand
and bruised arm.

1367
01:02:31.497 --> 01:02:34.834
and I said. "I'm gonna
make this count for you."

1368
01:02:34.917 --> 01:02:36.294
And that's what I've done.

1369
01:02:36.335 --> 01:02:38.045
You don't get
to knock my child down

1370
01:02:38.129 --> 01:02:42.300
and silence that voice
without 500 more raising up.

1371
01:02:42.341 --> 01:02:44.051
Other than that.
I'm kinda done with him.

1372
01:02:44.135 --> 01:02:45.970
and I'm moving on with my life.

1373
01:02:46.053 --> 01:02:47.805
I have things to do.

1374
01:02:47.847 --> 01:02:53.644
♪

1375
01:02:53.728 --> 01:02:56.856
(truck honking)

1376
01:02:56.939 --> 01:02:59.484
(cheering)

1377
01:02:59.525 --> 01:03:02.111
♪

1378
01:03:02.153 --> 01:03:04.864
We made it back to Texas!

1379
01:03:04.947 --> 01:03:14.874
♪

1380
01:03:32.850 --> 01:03:34.644
It feels kinda foreign.

1381
01:03:34.685 --> 01:03:36.771
Because it isn't
home anymore. you know.

1382
01:03:36.854 --> 01:03:39.190
Mm-hm.

1383
01:03:39.273 --> 01:03:41.192
Heavenly Father.
thank You for this day.

1384
01:03:41.234 --> 01:03:42.819
and thank You for
Erin and Dave.

1385
01:03:42.860 --> 01:03:45.530
and all the adventures
that they have been on.

1386
01:03:45.613 --> 01:03:48.157
Father. I thank You
for bringing us all

1387
01:03:48.199 --> 01:03:49.158
together through the years.

1388
01:03:49.200 --> 01:03:50.868
We love you so much. amen.

1389
01:03:50.952 --> 01:03:52.203
Amen.

1390
01:03:52.286 --> 01:03:53.746
So we would get to a new state.

1391
01:03:53.830 --> 01:03:55.289
we'd park. and hook up.
and all that.

1392
01:03:55.373 --> 01:03:56.374
and then we would
just kinda start

1393
01:03:56.457 --> 01:03:57.708
learning about
where in the heck we are.

1394
01:03:57.792 --> 01:03:58.918
Sometimes we'd
pull up in places.

1395
01:03:59.001 --> 01:04:00.378
and we'd know nothing.

1396
01:04:00.461 --> 01:04:01.879
What are the big stories here?

1397
01:04:01.921 --> 01:04:03.840
What are the areas of division?

1398
01:04:03.881 --> 01:04:05.591
It's just something
different everywhere.

1399
01:04:05.675 --> 01:04:07.426
-and then you'd find out--
-You didn't find one

1400
01:04:07.510 --> 01:04:09.387
central theme necessarily.

1401
01:04:09.428 --> 01:04:12.265
or it felt different
every single place you went?

1402
01:04:12.348 --> 01:04:14.267
You know. the biggest
disparities that we saw

1403
01:04:14.350 --> 01:04:16.435
were against Blacks.
and against Natives.

1404
01:04:16.519 --> 01:04:18.062
And we weren't looking--

1405
01:04:18.104 --> 01:04:18.729
It wasn't like we went in.

1406
01:04:21.440 --> 01:04:23.442
It was just like.
"What's the story?"

1407
01:04:23.526 --> 01:04:25.611
And we would find
in every single city

1408
01:04:25.695 --> 01:04:29.615
-this tragic story.
-And so. I think what we found

1409
01:04:29.699 --> 01:04:31.242
in this country

1410
01:04:31.325 --> 01:04:34.245
we've never been forced
to deal with the things

1411
01:04:34.287 --> 01:04:36.247
that have caused

1412
01:04:36.330 --> 01:04:37.874
to where we are today.

1413
01:04:37.915 --> 01:04:39.166
And so to heal them.

1414
01:04:39.250 --> 01:04:41.711
we have to go pretty far back.

1415
01:04:41.752 --> 01:04:44.589
Did you ever meet anybody
that didn't wanna talk to you?

1416
01:04:44.672 --> 01:04:48.217
So we're in Savannah. Georgia
kinda early on in our trip.

1417
01:04:48.259 --> 01:04:50.761
and I'm reaching out to this guy

1418
01:04:50.845 --> 01:04:53.931
who's a real kind of
community leader in Savannah.

1419
01:04:54.015 --> 01:04:55.933
-African American gentleman.
-African American guy.

1420
01:04:55.975 --> 01:04:57.768
he's 85 years old.

1421
01:04:57.852 --> 01:04:59.395
He's lived in Georgia
his whole life.

1422
01:04:59.437 --> 01:05:03.024
so he's seen lots
in his days in Georgia.

1423
01:05:03.107 --> 01:05:05.109
And he goes. "David.

1424
01:05:05.151 --> 01:05:07.069
you know. even if
I had time to meet with you.

1425
01:05:07.111 --> 01:05:09.447
-I don't think I would."
-Oh. okay.

1426
01:05:09.530 --> 01:05:11.949
-I was like. "Okay. all right."
-Did he give a reason?

1427
01:05:11.991 --> 01:05:14.410
He goes. "It's hard
to be reconciled

1428
01:05:14.452 --> 01:05:17.038
with someone who has
a boot on your neck."

1429
01:05:17.121 --> 01:05:18.873
-Wow.
-That is not

1430
01:05:18.956 --> 01:05:21.500
the America that
I believed that I lived in.

1431
01:05:21.584 --> 01:05:25.796
He saw me as
a white guy outsider

1432
01:05:25.880 --> 01:05:28.591
walking up to him
standing over here

1433
01:05:28.633 --> 01:05:30.134
where he's got
a boot on his neck.

1434
01:05:30.217 --> 01:05:32.553
And for me to
come up to him and say.

1435
01:05:32.637 --> 01:05:35.139
"Hey. can't we all
just get along?"

1436
01:05:35.181 --> 01:05:38.976
But before we do that.
we've gotta deal with the boot.

1437
01:05:39.018 --> 01:05:43.314
I had to realize
that he associated me

1438
01:05:43.397 --> 01:05:47.026
with the man
standing on top of him.

1439
01:05:47.109 --> 01:05:50.154
So has it changed how you vote?

1440
01:05:50.196 --> 01:05:52.949
Or whether you vote at all?

1441
01:05:52.990 --> 01:05:55.993
Um. I think it will
change the way I vote.

1442
01:05:56.035 --> 01:05:59.580
but I don't think
I'm Democrat now.

1443
01:05:59.664 --> 01:06:01.540
I'm not drawn to either party.

1444
01:06:01.624 --> 01:06:03.542
I think they're both
part of the problem.

1445
01:06:03.626 --> 01:06:05.586
So. I voted for Donald Trump

1446
01:06:05.670 --> 01:06:07.546
in the last
presidential election.

1447
01:06:07.630 --> 01:06:10.508
I wasn't wild about
either candidate.

1448
01:06:10.591 --> 01:06:11.592
but I will never vote

1449
01:06:14.345 --> 01:06:16.389
I'll vote for a human being

1450
01:06:16.472 --> 01:06:17.932
who I resonate with.

1451
01:06:18.015 --> 01:06:21.894
Where are you gonna
take the RV and go next?

1452
01:06:21.978 --> 01:06:26.983
We're gonna drive the RV
from Dallas

1453
01:06:27.024 --> 01:06:28.192
to Charlottesville.

1454
01:06:28.275 --> 01:06:32.238
Okay. And why Charlottesville?

1455
01:06:32.321 --> 01:06:34.907
I don't know is
probably my best answer.

1456
01:06:34.991 --> 01:06:38.494
We've just seen
the doors open there.

1457
01:06:38.536 --> 01:06:41.205
And so. that's
where we're goin'.

1458
01:06:41.247 --> 01:06:43.249
Okay. let's raise a toast

1459
01:06:43.332 --> 01:06:45.960
to the deep treasures

1460
01:06:46.043 --> 01:06:48.045
that you have discovered

1461
01:06:48.129 --> 01:06:49.922
in all 50 states.

1462
01:06:50.006 --> 01:06:52.466
-God bless America.
-Yeah. amen!

1463
01:06:52.550 --> 01:06:54.135
-Cheers!
-Cheers.

1464
01:06:54.218 --> 01:06:55.177
Cheers to that.

1465
01:06:55.219 --> 01:06:56.804
Thank you for tellin' me that.

1466
01:06:56.887 --> 01:07:01.100
♪

1467
01:07:01.183 --> 01:07:02.018
People around the country

1468
01:07:05.146 --> 01:07:07.398
where early posts
still have the candidates

